entry.def: If something or someone is untested, they have not yet been tried out or have not yet experienced a particular situation, so you do not know what they will be like.

example.ex: The Egyptian Army remained an untested force...
example.tran: 埃及军队依然有待考验。

example.ex: All of us were untested for what lay ahead.
example.tran: 将要面对的事情是大家都没有经历过的。

entry.tran: 未经检验的；未经测试的
entry.def: If you describe something such as a drug or chemical as untested, you mean that it has not been subject to scientific tests to find out if it is safe to use.

example.ex: ...the dangers of giving untested drugs to people.
example.tran: 把未经检验的药物给人吃的危险

means.word_mean: 1. not tried or tested by experience;
2. not yet proved or subjected to testing;
